Caleshan society is split between "mobile tribes" and "sedentary tribes"; mobile tribes are the baseline for Caleshan society, with many sedentary communities developing out of a specific mobile tribe, and mobile tribes possessing much of the influence over society due to their more active lifestyle and engagement with a wider array of enterprises. Despite this, sedentary tribes are more populous, and are responsible for the construction and maintenance of most of the 'real'', permanent buildings within Caleshan.
